\title{drmSEM: Distributional Piecewise Structural Equation Modelling on drmTMB}
\description{
drmSEM adds a structural-equation-modelling layer on top of the \code{drmTMB}
fitting engine. Each endogenous node is one \code{drmTMB} fit; drmSEM extracts the
component-labelled graph, validates it as a DAG, and provides path tables,
d-separation tests, and simulation-based direct, indirect, and total effects.
}
\details{
Causal paths are \strong{component-labelled}: a predictor may target the expected
response (\code{mu}), residual scale (\code{sigma}), shape (\code{nu}), zero-inflation
(\code{zi}), hurdle probability (\code{hu}), random-effect scale (\code{sd(group)}), or
bivariate residual correlation (\code{rho12}) of a node. Indirect effects can flow
through a mediator's mean (mean-mediated) or its distribution
(distribution-mediated), and are always computed by simulation rather than by
coefficient products.
}
\section{Engine vs layer}{

\code{drmTMB} is the model-fitting engine; \code{drmSEM} is the graph, SEM,
d-separation, path, and effect-decomposition layer. drmSEM never fits its own
likelihoods.
}

